-- Human Genome Sciences Consultant Accused of Tipping Hedge Fund Gets Bail
-- B y   D o n a l d   J e f f r e y   a n d   P a t r i c i a   H u r t a d o
-- 2010-11-17T16:23:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/human-genome-sciences-consultant-accused-of-tipping-hedge-fund-gets-bail.html
Dr. Yves Benhamou, a Human Genome
Sciences Inc. consultant accused of tipping off employees of a
hedge fund about the results of trials involving the hepatitis-C
drug Albuferon, was granted $3 million bail by a judge in New
York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donald Jeffrey in New York at 
